latestIgtvVideos.title: Shield 30 💓
#PrakatBirthday #Giveaway 🎂
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
✨Hi everyone! 
It’s that time of the year again! I’ve always been extremely excited to celebrate my birthday. I would spend my birthday doing things that gave me happiness like going to the blue cross, an orphanage , to donate and spend some time with them & throw myself the perfect birthday bash! But this year, due to the pandemic, I won’t be able to do any of the things that are now birthday traditions. So I’ve decided to start a new tradition. A series of birthday month giveaways for you! I’m so grateful for the love, kind words and inspiration that you guys send my way daily. You guys have been there with me through this difficult year, and I want to say thank you and give back. 

So drumroll pleaaase! It’s time to announce the first #PrakAtBirthday #Giveaway! Anyone who knows me or follows me, knows my skin doctor @theabhiinc She and @tr_skinclinic truly helped me transform my acne prone skin to clear and glowy skin, giving me oh so much extra confidence. And I would love to be able to help someone else feel the same way! The first giveaway rules will be up on the next post which will be up by tom :) 
All the best guys and thank you for being a part of my life! ✨🙏🎂❤️ #igtv #december #decemberbirthday #adecembertoremember #birthdaygiveaway #chennai

latestIgtvVideos.title: Prakatwork x Sukra
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
So thrilled to have done this collab with Sukra for their new bridal collection! @sukra_jewellery 

I absolutely believe that silver is the new gold! It’s inexpensive in comparison to gold, while still having a resale value (unlike artificial jewellery). Plus, with the right designs, it is just as gorgeous or even exceeding in beauty than most gold jewellery. 
 
Sukra, the silver retail brand that is famous for their Silverware, Valuable gifts and Temple Jewellery collection have launched a new range called “Kaaviyam”. And this collection is definitely aimed to make all your bridal jewellery dreams come true! 

I have showcased some of my favourite pieces from the collection in this video & styled it along with mom’s beautiful green silk saree.

I hope you guys enjoy the video and also check out Sukra’s new collection in their flagship store in mylapore. They’re following all required safety precautions to give you a safe and sanitised shopping experience! ✨❤️💄💋 #prakatwork #lotd #motd #jewelry #indianjewellery #silver #silverjewellery #bridalcollection #bridesofindia #southindian #shopping #shoplocal #shoponinstagram #makeuptutorial #igtv

latestIgtvVideos.title: 💙💜Coloured liner & Bright lips💜💙
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
✨#throwbackthursday to one of my all time fav looks that I had shot in a flow, without even planning what to do before I sat to shoot. 

This was shot almost 2 years back when I suffering from very pigmented acne marks ( those new to my Instagram have to #seeittobelieveit)😮 

It’s the reason I used foundation & concealer in my routine back then, whereas these days I mostly use ONLY concealers! 

I had posted the full length #youtube #makeuptutorial on my channel #prakatwork, but I’m editing the video tonight for #igtv & will be posting it tom. So those who have not seen it can have a sneak peak :)

Until then, here are the
PRODUCTS USED FOR THIS TUTORIAL: 

🌟Revlon Photoready Anti shine Primer @revlon 

🌟NYx Total Control Drop foundation in 12 & 14 (classic tan & golden tan) @nyxcosmetics_in 

🌟Nyx stay matte but not flat powder foundation in 10 Caramel @nyxcosmetics_in 

🌟Nyx lid lingerie shadow palette in for eyes 
 
🌟Huda beauty @hudabeautyshop @hudabeauty Giselle lashes

♥Disclaimer : I was Given most of the products for free by @nyxcosmetics_in for taking part in their faceawards but it was not a paid post. They're just few of my favourite products that work best for this look & so many more! Their liquid drop is one of my most fav water based foundations & @maccosmeticsindia ‘s concealer palette is a must have even in my makeup kit =)

latestPosts.caption:
🧿Manifesting Magic! 🧿✨ 

Back in 2019, I met the stunning Nayanthara ma’am @nayanthara at a private event. Even though I never ask celebrities for selfies (unless I’ve worked with them!), I took a chance that summer.  This picture was my way of manifesting - a visual reminder to one day do her makeup. 

Fast forward to 2024! The universe aligned and I had the incredible honor of doing her makeup in Chennai for Hello Magazine India! (Swipe to see the 2019 manifestation pic!) ➡️

Prayers, unwavering belief, and relentless hard work have always been my guiding light. ✨ This experience is proof that anything is possible with pure intentions and a clear conscience. 
As I always say with every milestone in my 14 year career. 

This is just the beginning. I’m fueled by the desire to keep growing, keep learning, and never give up.  Sending that same energy to all of you! Chase your dreams, big or small, and never let the flame of passion die out. 

#Nayanthara #HelloMagazineIndia #MakeupDreamsComeTrue #ManifestationJourney #GratefulHeart #MakeupMagic #SouthIndianGlam #DreamsDoComeTrue #NeverGiveUp #Inspiration #VisionBoardGoals #PositiveVibes ✨🧿🧿🧿

latestPosts.caption:
🌸🌸🌸
When you’re the makeup artist for your dearest friend’s wedding, it’s more than just a beautiful glam—it’s deeply personal.✨

From knowing Sruthi through her partner (my childhood bestie) to watching their journey from first date to forever, being part of this magical, intimate wedding was an honor I’ll always cherish. 💍💫
Creating her bridal look—simple, natural, traditional, and uniquely her—was my love letter to our friendship. 💄❤️
